supposed to know that?
(machinery beeps)

03:02.483 --> 03:04.249
Well, I'm sure reycraft
knew the answer.

03:04.251 --> 03:06.251
Yeah, whatever. That guys
is so tightly wound

03:06.253 --> 03:08.187
He probably reads
flash cards in the shower.

03:08.189 --> 03:10.222
Well, dr. Bell is
an amazing surgeon.

03:10.224 --> 03:13.192
Yeah, but she blows
as a person.
I just need to get better.

03:13.194 --> 03:17.596
(machinery beeping)

03:17.598 --> 03:19.731
Catheter in?
Catheter's in.

03:19.733 --> 03:21.366
Any complications?
No.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.468
B.P.'s steady.
Heart rate normal.

03:23.470 --> 03:25.604
Getting ready to deploy
the valve.

03:25.606 --> 03:27.372
(hissing)

03:27.374 --> 03:28.974
(beep)

03:28.976 --> 03:31.610
(hissing stops, click)

03:31.612 --> 03:32.744
Valve deployed.

03:32.746 --> 03:34.479
(rapid beeping)

03:34.481 --> 03:36.615
Pig is tanking, reid.
What are you gonna do?

03:36.617 --> 03:38.217
Uh, do an angio.

03:38.219 --> 03:39.751
Uh, make sure I haven't
blocked the coronaries.

03:39.753 --> 03:41.386
(stammers)
you've got tombstones
on your e.K.G.,

03:41.388 --> 03:42.821
So you might want to keep
your pig alive

03:42.823 --> 03:44.623
While you do your sleuthing.
(sighs)

03:44.625 --> 03:45.791
(monitor flatlining)

03:45.793 --> 03:47.759
Dr. Reid, your pig
is in v-fib.

03:47.761 --> 03:49.628
(clatters)
(alex) okay.

03:51.664 --> 03:53.732
(panting)

03:53.734 --> 03:55.534
(beeping)

03:55.536 --> 03:57.736
(continues panting)

03:58.805 --> 04:02.374
(buzzing)

04:02.376 --> 04:03.642
(monitor flatlining)

04:03.644 --> 04:06.278
I think I killed my pig.

04:06.280 --> 04:08.347
You deployed your valve
too high.

04:08.349 --> 04:09.648
You gave your pig
a heart attack.

04:09.650 --> 04:11.717
(beeping stops)
now if this were
a real patient,

04:11.719 --> 04:13.685
Dr. Reid would be spending
the next three years

04:13.687 --> 04:15.420
In legal depositions.

04:15.422 --> 04:17.522
Sloppy work,
but thank you

04:17.524 --> 04:19.591
For giving us all
a teachable moment.

04:19.593 --> 04:20.926
(beep)

04:20.928 --> 04:23.262
I have two pigs?
(woman) no.

04:23.264 --> 04:24.796
(indistinct conversations)

04:24.798 --> 04:26.598
(alex sighs)

04:29.035 --> 04:30.435
Charlie.
Dawn.

04:30.437 --> 04:32.371
You got my message?
Yes.

04:32.373 --> 04:34.439
How are you?
Wow, you look great.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.341
Uh, thank you.
I-I feel good, dawn.

04:36.343 --> 04:38.577
How's, uh,
hope zion treating you?

04:38.579 --> 04:39.811
It's good.

04:39.813 --> 04:42.047
I mean, they still haven't
got my parking spot,

04:42.049 --> 04:43.882
But, um, it's familiar.

04:43.884 --> 04:45.784
Feels like home.

04:45.786 --> 04:47.686
Hey.
Hey.

04:47.688 --> 04:49.721
How'd it, uh, go?

04:49.723 --> 04:51.290
I killed my pig.

04:51.292 --> 04:54.026
Ooh. Call the <i>hambulance.</i>
<i>(chuckles)</i>

04:54.028 --> 04:57.663
Dawn, what, uh, what did
you page me about?

04:57.665 --> 04:59.965
Well, um, you're gonna
think this is ridiculous,

04:59.967 --> 05:01.700
Because it is.

05:01.702 --> 05:04.369
But I finally sold
the condo,

05:04.371 --> 05:06.438
And one of the movers
found this

05:06.440 --> 05:08.440
Behind one of the cabinets.

05:11.077 --> 05:12.678
Peggy's cove.

05:12.680 --> 05:15.480
That was an amazing thing
that you did that weekend.

05:15.482 --> 05:19.384
This, uh, dog was drowning,
and I rescued it.

05:19.386 --> 05:20.719
Anybody would have
done that, dawn.

05:20.721 --> 05:22.654
It's no big deal.
He's being humble.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.089
I'm sure he is.

05:24.091 --> 05:27.092
You should get him to
tell you the story sometime.

05:27.094 --> 05:28.994
I just thought maybe
you would want to have it,

05:28.996 --> 05:30.796
For memory's sake.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.667
Joel.
Hey.

05:35.669 --> 05:37.002
Uh, how's that o.R.
Schedule coming?

05:37.004 --> 05:39.404
Uh, the same.

05:39.406 --> 05:42.641
Yeah, it's amazing we ever
got on without him.

05:43.943 --> 05:47.012
Nice lobster.

05:47.014 --> 05:50.615
(inhales)

05:50.617 --> 05:53.552
(velcro rips)
8 1/2. Ohio state.

05:53.554 --> 05:54.553
Okay.

05:54.555 --> 05:56.621
Oy. Uh, 48, uh...
Sam?

05:56.623 --> 05:59.424
Uh... Over. Nickel.
(whispers) okay.

05:59.426 --> 06:00.992
(normal voice) done. Done.

06:00.994 --> 06:03.795
(beep)
done. Don't look at me
in that tone of voice.

06:03.797 --> 06:05.130
Turn off the phone, sam.

06:05.132 --> 06:07.532
(click)
what's the problem, sam?

06:07.534 --> 06:10.702
Uh, they were giving me
this, you know--the thing.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.104
The ct.

06:12.106 --> 06:14.406
I got a terrible pain.

06:15.441 --> 06:16.775
(clicks pen)
so me where it hurts.

06:16.777 --> 06:19.778
(inhales) I thought
you'd never ask.

06:19.780 --> 06:22.681
It's all yours.
Oh. (laughs) you rascal.

06:22.683 --> 06:25.517
(groans) if I'd known
I'd live this long...

06:25.519 --> 06:27.719
(groans) I would have taken
better care of myself.

06:27.721 --> 06:30.522
You're only 55.
Are you kidding?

06:30.524 --> 06:31.990
That's 112 in hustler years.

06:31.992 --> 06:33.725
<i>(cell phone ringtone</i>
<i>plays "call to the post")</i>

06:33.727 --> 06:35.427
Oh, sorry.
I thought I turned that off.

06:35.429 --> 06:36.928
Dr. Lin.
I thought I turned it off.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.063
Phone.

06:38.065 --> 06:40.132
(groans) no--

06:40.134 --> 06:42.167
Ahh! There goes
my livelihood.

06:42.169 --> 06:43.902
She's usually a lot nicer
than this.

06:43.904 --> 06:45.971
What happened, you kill someone
this morning?

06:45.973 --> 06:48.507
No way.

06:48.509 --> 06:50.075
What are the odds?

06:50.077 --> 06:51.576
(gloves snap)

06:51.578 --> 06:53.812
He has some
lower abdominal pain.

06:53.814 --> 06:56.515
Let me guess.
That's not good.

06:56.517 --> 06:57.916
It's nothing conclusive.

06:57.918 --> 06:59.918
Give you even money
it's cancer.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.920
Yeah, I'm pretty sure
I'm not supposed to wager

07:01.922 --> 07:03.455
On a patient's pathology.

07:03.457 --> 07:05.190
Dr. Reid?
Smart.

07:05.192 --> 07:07.692
Save your money.
My lifestyle.

07:07.694 --> 07:09.961
The question isn't "why me?"
but "why not me"?

07:09.963 --> 07:11.763
(all laugh)

07:11.765 --> 07:13.165
(monitor beeping rapidly)
(groaning and coughing)

07:13.167 --> 07:15.033
Sam?
Lie back, mr. Roth.

07:15.035 --> 07:16.501
Jeez. I can't breathe!

07:16.503 --> 07:17.836
I think he's having
a heart attack.

07:17.838 --> 07:19.504
(groans)

07:22.875 --> 07:24.576
Emma nolan. I treated her
two months ago

07:24.578 --> 07:25.911
